Field.Name: N2Homeownorrent
Field.PromptText: 2. Do you rent or own your home?

Field.Name: N4Peopleinhouse
Field.PromptText: 4. How many people live in this house?

Field.Name: N5Howprepared
Field.PromptText: 5. How prepared do you feel your household is to handle a disaster or emergency?

Field.Name: N6EmergencyPlan

Field.Name: N9PrescriptionMeds3Day

Field.PromptText: 10. Are you familiar with the phrase "shelter in place?"

Field.PromptText: 11. If asked to evacuate by local authorities, would you leave your home?

Field.Name: N12evacuationdestination
Field.PromptText: 12. If you would evacuate, do you know where you would go?

Field.Name: N13pets
Field.PromptText: 13. Do you or anyone in your household have pets, service animals, or livestock?

Field.Name: N14evacuatepets
Field.PromptText: 14. If asked to evacuate, what would you do with your pets?

Field.Name: N15Preparedness_messages
Field.PromptText: 15. Where do you normally hear or receive disaster preparedness information? (check all that apply)

Field.Name: N16Disaster_infosource

Field.Name: N18Deliveries1

Field.PromptText: dialysis or other frequent medical care

Field.Name: N18Full_time_car
Field.PromptText: full-time care because of medical or other conditions

Field.Name: N19hospitalseekmedicalcare
Field.PromptText: 19. If you had to transport yourself or one of your household members to receive healthcare during an emergency, where would you seek care?

Field.Name: N20CODetector
Field.PromptText: 20. Does your home have a working carbon monoxide detector?

Field.Name: N21NoCODetector
Field.PromptText: 21. What is the one main reason for not having a working carbon monoxide detector in your home?

Field.PromptText: 22. Are you aware of your county's outdoor emergency alert/siren system?

Field.Name: N23sirens
Field.PromptText: 23. Can you hear those sirens (for storms, flooding, etc.) from directly outside your home?
